# IT Disposal Policy

Janus Healthcare Partners utilizes a dedicated IT to dispose of all physical IT assets (employee workstations) that have reached the end of their lifespane.  Note: all sensative data is stored on cloud servers hosted by AWS and not on local workstation hard drives.  Use of removeable media or external hard drives is explictly prohibited.

## IT Disposal Requirements

1. All physical IT assets (ie. employee workstations) are returned to the dedicated IT team when they reach end of life status
2. All software liscenses are uninstalled and employee access is removed
3. The workstation harddrive is re-imaged clearing it of any data
4. The workstation is recycled as is required by local law governing waste disposal
